      "text": "I, James P. Breckenridge, Clerk of the County Court within and for the County and State aforesaid, do hereby certify that H. Y. Park Esq., before whom the foregoing affidavit, was made, and who has thereto signed his name, was, at the time of so doing, a (2) Notary Public in and for the County and State above named, duly commissioned, qualified and sworn, that all of his official acts as such are entitled to full faith and credit, and that his said signature, as it appears on the reverse page hereof is genuine",
