      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Remarks:—In case the Deputy authorizes the Clerk's certificate, evidence may be required to show that the Deputy is duly appointed and authorized by law to sign the Clerk's name and use the seal of the Court—therefore it is better to have the Clerk's own individual authorifications at once; and thus save the number and expense of a general authorization certificate respecting the Deputy, which might be required if the papers were authenticated by him instead of the Clerk.",
